    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Liatris squarrosa are inflammation, fever, and skin irritation, which are effectively reduced by the plant's anti-inflammatory and antipyretic properties. The plant's antiseptic and antibacterial properties also make it an effective treatment for respiratory issues, fungal infections, diarrhea, and wounds. Its antifungal and antimicrobial properties further aid in the treatment of bronchitis, infections, and wound healing. Additionally, Liatris squarrosa has been shown to alleviate rheumatism, allergies, eczema, and cough, while also possessing antidiabetic properties that help regulate diabetes. Furthermore, the plant's expectorant properties help relieve cough, gastroenteritis, asthma, and pneumonia, as well as reducing pain and promoting wound healing.",
