    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Liatris squarrosa are its antimicrobial activity, which is attributed to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones and phenolic compounds, while its anti-inflammatory property is associated with flavonoids and saponins that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. This plant also possesses antioxidant properties, which are largely due to the presence of phenolic acids and flavonoids that scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Additionally, Liatris squarrosa exhibits antibacterial activity, primarily as a result of the action of sesquiterpene lactones that disrupt bacterial cell membranes and inhibit the production of virulence factors. Furthermore, the plant's analgesic property can be attributed to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones that inhibit the production of pain mediators and modulate the activity of pain-sensing neurons. The bioactive compounds responsible for these medicinal properties are diverse and include volatile oils, terpenoids, and phenolic compounds that work synergistically to exert their therapeutic effects.",
