    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Liatris squarrosa are tincture, tea, infusion, salve, and infused oil. A tincture is made by soaking the roots and rhizomes in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to extract its bioactive compounds. Tea and infusion are prepared by steeping the flowers or leaves in hot water to produce a liquid extract that can be used for medicinal purposes. A salve is prepared by infusing the roots in a carrier oil like olive or coconut oil and then mixing it with beeswax to create a topical balm for skin issues. Infused oil is made by steeping the plant material in a carrier oil, which is often used as a topical treatment for wounds, inflammation, and skin irritations.",
